 A SUPERFIT jogger who was knocked down by a cyclist has died . 
 Newlywed Peter Craig, 49, was struck when he was out running about a mile from his home in Livingston on Saturday. 
 At first, his injuries only appeared minor but he was later taken to hospital where it was found he had serious brain injuries . 
Peter was declared brain dead but was being kept alive yesterday so his organs could be donated.
It is understood that the cyclist involved in the accident has now come forward following a police appeal to trace him.

